Arbitrary Python code can be used in modules at compile time, for an example to transform input parameters: sample_dly_len = round ( sample_rate delay ) fifo_depth = ceil_pow2 ( sample_dly_len ) feedback_gain_fixp = samples . dtype ( feedback_gain ) Rest of the echo function code describes the hardware module for applying echo audio effect to the input Modules are instantiated using function calls: decouple(dout, depth=fifo_depth) , which return module output interfaces that can in turn be passed as arguments to other module functions in order to make a connection between the For conveniance the pipe "|" operator can be used to pass output of one function as argument to the next This was used to connect the output of decouple to prefill ( "\" is used just to split the line visually): feedback = decouple ( dout , depth = fifo_depth ) \ | prefill ( dtype = samples . dtype , num = sample_dly_len ) Again, the echo function returns its output interfaces which is then used to establish the connection with the next module that received the echo o

journey in preclinical This is the stage of research that occurs after drug conceptualization and before clinical The primary goal is to determine the drug’s feasibility, interactive properties, and overall safety If the researchers and regulatory authorities believe the drug has potential and a relatively low , it then proceeds to clinical research, or testing in Clinical Trials In this stage, researchers discover how drugs interact with the human Clinical trials follow a typical series from early, Phase I studies to , large scale Phase III If a drug proves to be safe and effective throughout it’s journey, it is then submitted to the FDA for approval to hopefully one day make it to market and benefit millions of patients We specialize in these trials and provide unparalleled services to sponsoring pharmaceutical When we believe we’ve found the right trial, the real search begins—in the Patient Engagement and Community Outreach This is where you come Every trial has very specific and unique eligibility requirements for patients ranging from age to medical history to current We apply our expertise to reach the appropriate patient populations in our communities through OpenRelay - Products Open Relay Menu Explore OpenRelay We ve created some remarkable products you can fork and build on, or just use right now! OpenRelay In case you didn t know, OpenRelay the company is powered by OpenRelay the software! OpenRelay (the software) is an open order book built on a powerful open source microservice architecture that makes finding orders and filling them via the Protocol fast and efficient at any We run our own instance of the software to power our business, but because it s open source, you can stand up your own instance and independently operate a relay tailored to your specific Want to see how it works? Check it out on Github! Documentation View on Github Embiggen Embiggen (MBGN) is the ERC20 token that grows in your wallet! It offers a way to introduce new currency by providing it to all MBGN holders at once, proportionally to the amount of MBGN they hold (at a rate of % per annum, compounded hourly). You can think of it like a stock split the total supply of the token is increased while each holder s share of the pie stays the same View Contract Claim Embiggen! NotCoin NotCoin is an ERC20 token that enables "one-sided" In otherwords, if you want to use an exchange contract to offer a token (such as Embiggen) without asking for a different token in return, NotCoin gets the job OpenRelay invented NotCoin to facilitate the Embiggen Airdrop, because we literally wanted to give away Hypothetically though, it could be used in any exchange where a token is being offered in exchange for something other than a token (like payment via fiat currency, for example). View Contract Blog Post Embiggen Airdrop dApp We developed the Embiggen Airdrop dApp to enable users to claim The dApp is meant to prepare people for token trading by walking them through the process of setting up a web3 enabled browser, acquiring the necessary ETH, and claiming Embiggen in just a few easy By the time they have claimed some Embiggen, they have everything they need to get deeper into the decentralized trading About the UX Try it out! Fling! Fling is a dApp for sending tokens to a lot of different addresses at once in just two The smart contract powering Fling was originally created to help us prepare for the Embiggen Airdrop, but after others expressed interest in a interface to the contract s functionality, we created the Fling More a love letter to the Ethereum community than a product, Fling demonstrates what is possible when clever smart contracts meet (Also, it has a pretty sweet trebuchet ) Blog Post Try it out! Affiliate Portal The OpenRelay Affiliate Portal dApp is a gateway that developers can use to 1) sign up for the OpenRelay Affiliates Program, and 2) view and redeem fees shared when dApps generate fees (we share % of fees generated by affiliates, with affiliates). The dApp allows developers to sign up, and then once they do, provides a dashboard interface to view and redeem Simple, no? Blog Post Try it out! Where to next? connected in meaningful ways and founded Project Connecting with the commitment to providing mental health care while providing the connection and community required to achieve optimum Lennie has experience working with individuals, couples, families and She specializes in care and is proficient working with depression, anxiety, emotion regulation, relationship issues, LGBTQA, adoption and Lennie is a certified facilitator and the Rocky Mountain Region Leader for The Daring Way™, a curriculum based on the research of Brené Lennie presented at The Daring Way s Courage Camp in and on incorporating care into the Daring Way™ ​ Lennie has worked as clinical director, trauma educator, and adoption Lennie was on an expert on a panel for the Utah Adoption Conference, was a speaker at the Utah Adoption Conference and has been a guest on webinars and Clinical Director Clinician Emily Dixon, CMHC ​​ Emily Dixon is a Clinical Mental Health Counselor with years of experience working with families to build resiliency, enhance coping skills and inspire She earned her undergraduate degree from the University of Redlands in Psychology, Outdoor Education and She was recruited to play Lacrosse and spent much of her senior year developing a Outdoor Program and Leadership After completing her undergraduate work, she spent six years guiding adventure trips with teenagers These were month long courses that focused on leadership, personal growth and She then moved to Utah to work in Wilderness Therapy where she assisted children in accessing their resilience to live healthier and happier She completed her master’s degree through Goddard College in Clinical Mental Health Counseling and has worked in community mental health as a crisis counselor and therapist for the last eight Working in homes with children and their families gave her a wonderful look at how family’s function in conflict and stress and the toll that individual struggle has on not just the child but the family as a She became interested in working with the school district as a child In addition to in home therapy she has spent the last four years working in the Salt Lake School District and Canyons School District as a therapist for a Elementary ​Emily’s areas of passion and expertise include advocating for children and their families, treating anxiety, depression, transition, grief, trauma, parenting, emotional regulation and social She uses evidence base approaches and works closely with kids to identify problems, develop strategies and make healthier Emily’s therapeutic influences include , Narrative, Experiential, and Play She is certified in Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing (EMDR) and experienced with Trauma Behavior Therapy (TF-CBT). Emily prides herself on her ability to connect with people, creating a safe environment where they can develop healthy choices to increase success in their psychosocial She works closely with families, teachers and community supports to understand developmental trauma and the deficits and struggles it has on Emily strongly believes that children do well if they can do well, and her role is to identify the deficits and increase the skills to broaden one’s Emily emphasizes the importance of connection, attachment and relationships and believes that increasing self awareness and self confidence is at the root of these Chief Operating Officer Therapist Tara Pennington, MFT Tara Pennington holds a master’s degree in Marriage and Family Therapy from Argosy University and was a double major at the University of Utah with degrees in Psychology as well as Human Development & Family Tara is trained in Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing Therapy (EMDR) and specializes in Autism Spectrum Disorders, depression, anxiety, trauma, and enjoys working with children, adolescents, adults, couples and families to foster connection and In addition to her therapy practice, Tara has also spent the past years aiding and developing programs for families who have children diagnosed with Autism Spectrum In , Tara founded Building Pathways which offers treatment programs for individuals and families that face Autism Spectrum Disorders and other developmental difficulties using Relationship Development Intervention (RDI®). Tara and Building Pathways were featured in The Autism File magazine in (Building pathways through The Autism File , , ). About the Charity | Harmony & Healing News Benefit Concert About About Harmony & Healing How It All Started Board of Directors Sponsor Thank Yous Policy Privacy Policy Contact Menu News Benefit Concert About About Harmony & Healing How It All Started Board of Directors Sponsor Thank Yous Policy Privacy Policy Contact Donate Now ABOUT THE CHARITY Harmony & Healing Information Why I Founded a Live Music Charity As a performing member of the platinum selling band BOSTON back in , I noticed how the people were mesmerized and transported back to their youth when listening to the great hits of I was intrigued that even the hardcore BOSTON fans didn’t seem to care who got out of the “spaceship” they only cared that you were reproducing this great music live that resurfaced old, warm memories and made them feel good . While on tour, I was fortunate to have the opportunity to perform live acoustic music for some sick children at Miller Children’s Hospital in Long Beach, These kids didn’t really know the BOSTON catalog, but they nonetheless truly seemed to appreciate the vibe and spirit of the music, and the fact that the performer was singing to them . At first shy, the children’s parents all eventually approached me and shyly asked, “Could you come play for my baby next?” As I met and played for more and more of the kids, I realized that the spirit of music and the feeling it communicated was a universal healing power that bypassed the brain and went straight to the soul of these unfortunate Walking out to the parking lot, I felt as if I were on Cloud 9, and had a flash of inspiration that I needed to use music to lift the spirits of the most fragile among us : hospital patients, their families, and loved Thus, the idea of Harmony & Healing was Founded in January, , Harmony & Healing is a hospital and healthcare facility music charity, and an (c)(3) charitable organization, founded by San Ramon resident and former BOSTON band member, David Our EIN is and our mailing address is: HARMONY & HEALING Bollinger Canyon Road Suite San Ramon, CA Our phone number is: See our policy here .
